# B308: /tasks in Telegram returns nothing

## Summary
The `/tasks` slash command in Telegram does not return anything (empty or no response).

## Acceptance Criteria
- `/tasks` in Telegram returns the current task tree for the session
- Empty task trees produce a helpful "no tasks" message rather than nothing
- Behavior matches other channels (Discord, Slack, HTTP) which handle Tasks correctly

## Investigation
- Slash_commands.handle "/tasks" returns Tasks (tested in test_slash_commands.ml)
- Telegram handler at src/telegram.ml:1545-1553 calls Task_tree.render_tree_with_legend
- Likely issue: empty tree produces empty string, or session_key mismatch, or render returns empty

## Files
- src/telegram.ml (handler)
- src/task_tree.ml (render_tree_with_legend)
- src/slash_commands.ml (command parsing)
